  "prompt": "Why wasn't John Williams hired to write the soundtrack to Rogue One?",
  "response": "John Williams, the renowned composer known for his iconic scores in the Star Wars saga and many other films, was not hired to score \"Rogue One: A Star Wars Story\" primarily due to scheduling conflicts. Williams was busy working on other projects during the time that \"Rogue One\" was in production. Instead, the film's score was composed by Michael Giacchino, who brought his own touch to the music while still incorporating themes and motifs associated with the Star Wars universe. Giacchino's work was well-received and helped to create a distinctive atmosphere for the film.",
